        This, as you may have guessed, is a blog about Pizza. We all love this delicious delicacy.
        Why not learn about it?
        <!--Content1-->
        <p>Pizza, as we know it, is bread topped with sauces, spices, vegetables, meat and most importantly... cheese!
      It is then baked in an oven and then served to excited customers.</p>      
        <h2>History of Pizza</h2>
        Pizza was once considered food for the poor. Many countries in the ancient times used to bake bread and 
        top it with spices and vegetables. This is now called Focaccia Bread. In Italy, many Street vendors used to bake pizza in the open.
        Labourers would eat pizza as they needed something cheap to fit their budget and satisfy their hunger.
        When Italy was made a country, the King and Queen decided to travel across tha country.
        When they reached the city of Naples, Queen Margerhita smelled the irresistable aroma of pizza baking on the streets.
        The Queen appointed a baker named Raffaele Esposita to bake a pizza for her. he was bewildered but decided to add Basil,
        Tomatoes and white mozzarella cheese ontpo it, making the first Margerhita Pizza!
        
        <h2>Types of Pizza</h2>
        There are many, many types of Pizza around the world. Different countrie and various toppings to their Pizza.
        In India, you can find, Tandoori Chicke pizza, Tandoori Butter Chicken Pizza, Cottage cheese(Paneer)Pizza, etc.
        In Hawaii, Pinapple is added onto pizza. This type of Pizza is debated as people think Pinapple does not belong on Pizza.
        
        <h2>Fun Facts</h2>
        <ol>
            Early versions of pizza were square or rectangular, not the round shape we typically associate with it today. 
            The Hawaiian pizza, with its pineapple topping, is actually a Canadian invention, created in Ontario in 1962. 
            In 2001, a pizza was delivered to the International Space Station, making it the first food to be eaten in space. 
        </ol>

